The search for new anthelmintic agents, especially those of botanical origin, has grown substantially due to the
perspective of less contamination of meat and milk, as well as other advantages related to their cost and
accessibility in less developed countries. The aim of this study was to evaluate the in vitro anthelmintic activity of
essential oils of the plant species
